He added: “I know their top scorer (Shirao) is down due to an injury but in case he comes in, I know how to handle him because I have done it before. Yes he is a good player but I have good defenders.”
In the other match of the day, Leads United will square it out with Upper Karen in the battle for third place. The winner of the tournament will receive a trophy and Sh70,000 cash prize, while the runners up will take home Sh50,000. The third and fourth place finishers will pocket Sh 30,000 and Sh20, 000 respectively.
Fixtures
Leads United v Upper Karen 10am
Gogo Boys v Ping FC    3pm  
